<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>
<title>WANDER-RANDOMLY-BY-TURNING</title>

</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I repeatedly turn left or right and move forward.</i> </h3>

	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	</p>
	<p><b>WANDER-RANDOMLY-BY-TURNING </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>add-behaviours list-of-micro-behaviours "Behaviours" [TURN-RANDOMLY.html MOVE-FORWARD.html] 
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>This combines

	<a title="TURN-RANDOMLY" href="TURN-RANDOMLY.html">

	TURN-RANDOMLY</a> and

	<a title="MOVE-FORWARD" href="MOVE-FORWARD.html">

	MOVE-FORWARD</a> to create a wandering behaviour.

	<a title="WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS" href="WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS.html">

	WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS</a> moves up, down, left, or right 

	rather than moving forward while turning a random amount. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>The

	<a title="TURN-RANDOMLY" href="TURN-RANDOMLY.html">

	TURN-RANDOMLY</a> changes my heading repeatedly while the

	<a title="MOVE-FORWARD" href="MOVE-FORWARD.html">

	MOVE-FORWARD</a> micro-behaviours makes me move forward in the direction I'm 

	headed. </p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>
</body>
</html>
